The "True Jesus Church" is an independent church that was established in 
Beijing, China in 1917. Today, there are approximately 1.5 million members in 
forty five countries. The church belongs to the Pentecostal branch of Christianity that emerged during the early Twentieth Century. Since 1990, the church was established in [[Samoa]]. They aim to preach the gospel to all nations before the Second Coming of Jesus. 

==The ten main beliefs of the church==
===Holy Spirit===
Receiving the Holy Spirit, evidenced by speaking in tongues, is the guarantee of our inheritance in the Kingdom of Heaven.

===Baptism===
They conduct Baptism in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ with the person's head facing downwards and fully immersed into natural living water. 

===Holy Communion===
"The Holy Communion is the sacrament to commemorate the death of the Lord Jesus Christ. Only one unleavened bread and grape juice is used".

